Former president Soeharto should meet his office's summons for undergoing further investigation on corruption cases, Indonesian Attorney General Marzuki Darusman said here on Friday.
Indonesian embassies in foreign countries will provide whatever assistance they can to the Attorney General's Office in investigating the wealth of former president Soeharto abroad, Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said here Tuesday.
The three main factions in Indonesia's House of Representatives have agreed that an official investigation into the wealth of former president Soeharto must be launched immediately and concluded before the turn of the century.
